The story of a seemingly normal middle school boy, who is actually looked down upon by his peers because he is deemed as crazy and mental. Why? text: Just finished the movie and I have to say I loved it. I got the originality and of course the comedy was cringy about 60% of the time, but it had more of a story to family and death that I think everyone will find sad. This is movie is for people looking for creativity mixed in with life, you make the most of life by making it your own, even in the toughest obstacles, you keep going because you never want to think "what if" this never happened. You want to explore until the end, yes its portrayed as a comedy, but it has a beautiful story of fighting for what's right even if the odds are against you. I hope people give this movie a chance. The acting was also pretty good, just to give a shoutout to the cast and especially the team behind this whole production.

text: I am 30 years old so I am no longer able to get into teen movies since they no longer have the same appeal they did back in the 90s.....but....I am glad to see that there is finally a newer movie out that is focusing on how teachers can be the biggest bullies of all....I had a hard time in school due to a major case of ADD and I did not take medication for it... also was always exhausted and falling asleep in school because my stepdad came home drunk and pissed off every night and felt the need to show me and my brother just how angry he was on the inside all hours of the night causing us to get very little sleep...then I became majorly depressed by age 14 and no longer wanted to live...it effected my school work tremendously but not once did any of my teachers ask why I was having a hard time focusing... all they did was pick on me and humiliate me in front of my classmates.What was really sick was I could totally tell they got off on it.It ultimately lead to me dropping out of school because I feared my teachers....I think it's great they made a comedy movie like this but I feel they should make a very serious drama about teachers that bully and make kids want to kill themselves.

text: Movie looks corny asf.   At my middle school there were 6 types of kids.   1. The drug kids. The ones who thought they were all grown smoking weed in the bathroom and drinking lean at the parks at like ages (12-14) like damn we ain’t even in high school yet.  2. The Sexually active kids. These kids kinda fell in with the drug kids sometimes. The ones grinding at the dances n shit. You know? The ones you would here about Monday morning at lunch like “omg did you know that she sucked him off at the back of the bus on the way home from six flags?”   3. The smart kids. Ones who always made highest of honor roll with a 4.0. Already thinking about college and shit.  4. The Likeable kids. Pretty mediocre in academics. Sometimes known as the ‘class clown’, always making the whole class laugh, sometimes good friends with the teacher, and had cool friend groups.  5. Athletic kids. The ones who would play all the sports not just for the school but for the city too. They had their own hangout spot at lunch.   6. The shy and quiet kids who also sometimes fell in within the smart kids group too . They were kids who had very little friends. Terrified of asking for anything. Gets anxiety when the teacher is like “well if there isn’t any volunteers I guess I’ll pull out the cards”. Always listening to music too. (That was me)
